		<div class="postbody">
			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: For the Sys Admins and Tech Ops folks...
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1789127">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							So, update.<br />
<br />
We had originally wanted to get operations on board with us before going to the upper management to present a unified front.  Since this would be a radical significant departure from the current corporate mandate (Can only deploy after midnight EST on Fridays), we wanted pretty much all technology fronts on board with this being a preferably idea to do the sale to management.<br />
<br />
We had the meeting.  They expressed similar frustrations that there's a mad rush for every application to deploy in the same time window and want to shuffle them around.  They also don't like how time consuming it is and how difficult it is to fix deploys when something inevitably goes wrong mid way through.  Unfortunately, they're not quite on board yet with more frequent deployments and want to get automated deployments in place across the board.  Which isn't a bad thing and definitely something that needs to (and probably should have already) happen.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
